messages.text: Dude, did your electricity just go out?
Nope. The storms not too bad over here. Yours?
Yeah… I’m pretty terrified right now
You do know this is like how 70% of horror movies start
Are you home alone?
Right now. My mom should be home in a few minutes though
Will you be my guide through this obvious nightmare I’m currently experiencing?
Haha of course
What am I even supposed to do without electricity?
How did people live like this? I can’t see anything
Go light some candles or something. See if you can find a flashlight.
All of my candles are lit and it just looks so much more terrifying.
Like I’m having some sort of séance or something. Ugggghhh I’m so bored.
You’ll be fine.
Should I like, read a book? Or just sit in a corner surrounded by flames until my mom gets back?
Where did she even go with the weather like this?
Who knows. She’s been acting so strange these past few months
How?
Like how she acted before my dad was sent away.
She’s just been so paranoid about everything and like, incredibly sad.
You mean more than usual?
Way more than usual.
Why? I thought that she was doing so much better since she started dating that businessman with the 1940s haircut.
She was until she broke up with him a couple of weeks ago.
Now she has become some weird type of hermit that will only leave the house to go grocery shopping every so often.
Haha what do you mean?
Since she ended the relationship with Mike, now, every weekend instead of being wined and dined...
she just stares out our front window through the blinds. Then remembers we need milk. She might be going crazy.
Really?!
Yeah, I mean last night I watched her walk back and forth to make sure that all of the windows and doors were shut
and locked at least 13 times before she went to bed.
P.S. I’m still in awe of our ancestors for living without the beautiful thing called electricity.
Thank you Benjamin Franklin.
She sounds like my mom after she binge watches those awful crime shows.
For real, it’s like she’s waiting for Michael Meyers to come to Mount Juliet.
She’s either losing her mind, or she’s hiding something from me. Including all of the flashlights. I can barely see anything right now
Open up some of the blinds.
Smart thinking, Ash.
Just stay away from the windows, I think we are under a tornado warning.
That’s weird.
What is?
Our house is the only one on the street that has no power.
Maybe it wasn’t the storms fault. Maybe there’s something wrong with your circuit breaker.
Or maybe my mom conveniently forgot to pay the power bill.
I don’t even know what a circuit breaker is.
HURRY UP MOM
Oh wait I think she’s here
Finally!
Did she get the lights turned back on?
Hello?
Haileyyyyyyyy
I could have sworn I heard the front door open
Is she not home yet?
No and I’m officially freaked out
You might just be hearing the wind. Have you tried calling her?
No, not yet
Call her maybe she’s just stuck in traffic.
Alright.
She didn’t answer.
I’m starting to get a little paranoid over here.
Just breathe. I’m sure she’s alright. Do you need me to come over?
I keep hearing footsteps downstairs.
I think someone is here.
It’s probably her. Just go check again.
ten minutes later
Is she home?
Just let me know if everything’s alright.
I’m leaving to come to your house in five minutes if you don’t respond.
She’s here.
Good. She’ll get the lights on soon, everything will be alright and we can start trying to find your mom a new man.
Maybe someone with an 1890s mustache?
Something weird is going on.
What?
My mom just told me to go to my room and lock my door.
She’s never done that before.
She’s probably just paranoid about the storm.
I don’t know. She was acting weird. Weirder than normal.
I think she’s screaming at someone.
On the phone?
I think someone else.
I can’t tell what’s going on.
Is it bad?
I don’t know I can’t tell, I can’t hear them. I have to go downstairs to check.
Listen to your mom, Hailey, and stay in your room.
She’s screaming.
Should you call the cops?
Something broke.
I keep hearing glass hit the floor.
Maybe it’s the storm, just stay calm.
I can hear her crying. I think she’s hurt. I need to help her I don’t know what to do
I’m calling the police right now they should be at your house soon.
Stay in your room and make sure the doors are locked! Keep in contact with me until they get there!
I don’t know.
It’s quiet now.
I can’t hear her anymore.
Something’s wrong
I have to go check on her.
Hailey stay where you are!!!!
I can hear footsteps.
Someone is coming up the stairs.
Stay quiet, Hailey!! The police said they’d be there as soon as possible!
He knows my name.
He knows me.
Hailey don’t move the cops should be there any moment please just stay safe!!!!
Hailey?!
Are you alright?
Please tell me that you’re alright!!!
It’s my dad.
Your dad?? I thought he lived in Canada or something, what are you talking about?!
omg he’s out.
out of where???
jail
what??!!!! what are you talking about, Hay??
He found us.
